    <item>
      <title>Re: Do the gods have limits to their influence on Norrath?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Lore&amp;message.id=11246#M11246</link>
      <description>&lt;P&gt;Any action by one god inevitably leads to another god acting elsewhere. The principle reason most of the gods came to Norath was to keep their other gods who came there in check.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The goals of the gods then is to establish the balance of power. If Innoruuk simply destroyed Tunare's creations, she woudl in turn destroy his. Both sides would in the end loose their position in Norath. Instead Inny establishes the balance of power. He gains a position in Norath while keeping the balance of power between them stable. If he went too far and outright destroyed all of Tunare's creation, she would be forced to create more (thus regaining her power) or outright destroy his, or both.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The Elfs migrate to the Faydwar, Ro gets his turf in the mountains, the humans appear. Despite the change, Tunare's original purpose remains and her creation survives (the Elfs seem to be doing well)&lt;/P&gt;</description>
