      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The ting about nuclear war is it's mutually assured destruction. If Inny wiped out Tunare's creations, she would have no choice but to retaliate or be forced to quit Norath altogether. The resulting conflict would likely end up with inny and Tunare neither gaining any headway.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;As it is, Tunare's creations in Norath are successful. The High Elfs have founded a good city and are influential throught the world, the Wood Elfs also have a good city and a founded operation in surefall to restore the forests. Their existance has had a huge influence on mankind, as they were in a position to give aid to the Marr's girl which led to the civilization of man and thus ultimately thwarting the plans of the gods imprisoning Mithanial Marr.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Had she actively opposed and retaliated against these orriginal threats, the Elfs may have been completely destroyed in the cross fire and their current position in Norath would be gone. The race of Man would have never reached it's current pinical, etc. &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;In short, subilty and maintaining the balance of power is far more effective for the gods then moving mountains.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
